<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>EJS Explained</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; }
        h1, h2 { color: #333; }
        code { background-color: #f4f4f4; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; }
        .container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
        .section { margin-bottom: 20px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Understanding EJS (Embedded JavaScript)</h1>

        <!-- BASIC OUTPUT -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Basic Output with <%= %></h2>
            <p>The <code>&lt;%= %&gt;</code> tag is used to output the value of a variable or a JavaScript expression into the HTML. It's the most common tag you'll use.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
            <p>Hello, <strong><%= name %></strong>!</p>
            <p>Your favorite number is: <strong><%= favoriteNumber %></strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- CONTROL FLOW -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Control Flow with <% %></h2>
            <p>The <code>&lt;% %&gt;</code> tag allows you to embed JavaScript logic like loops and conditionals directly into your HTML.</p>
            
            <h3>Conditionals (if/else)</h3>
            <% if (isRaining) { %>
                <p>It's raining! Don't forget your umbrella.</p>
            <% } else { %>
                <p>It's not raining. Enjoy the weather!</p>
            <% } %>

            <h3>Loops (for)</h3>
            <p>Here are your to-do items:</p>
            <ul>
                <% todos.forEach(function(todo) { %>
                    <li><%= todo %></li>
                <% }); %>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- INCLUDING PARTIALS -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Including Partials with <%- include %></h2>
            <p>The <code>&lt;%- include('partials/header') %&gt;</code> tag lets you include other EJS files (called partials) into your current template. This is great for reusing components like headers and footers.</p>
            <%- include('partials/header') %>
            <p>This content is in the main file.</p>
            <%- include('partials/footer') %>
        </div>

        <!-- UNESCAPED HTML -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. Unescaped HTML with <%- %></h2>
            <p>The <code>&lt;%- %&gt;</code> tag outputs unescaped HTML. Use this with caution, as it can be a security risk if the data is user-provided.</p>
            <p><strong>Escaped (default with <%= %>):</strong> <%= someHtml %></p>
            <p><strong>Unescaped (with <%- %>):</strong> <%- someHtml %></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
